    "Furthermore, it is evident that there are both many mismatches on the subpopulation level (which indicates low representativity), and clear preferences of each LLM for certain socio-demographics, preferences that seem to vary randomly across questions (indicative of machine bias).",
    "Note: BIC: Bayesian Information Criterion.",
    "Reading example: For Happiness with GPT-4-Turbo, the linear model of all the social conditioning variables accounts for 44% of the variance in LLM-WVS nEMD distances.",
